NBA, Players “Still Very Far Apart” After Seven Hours of Talks, Union Says

-- B y   M a s o n   L e v i n s o n
-- 
2011-10-01T22:21:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-01/nba-players-still-very-far-apart-after-seven-hours-of-talks-union-says.html
National Basketball Association  and
players union negotiators are “still very far apart” in
seeking to end its work stoppage, union lawyer  Jeffrey Kessler 
said after more than seven hours of talks today at a Manhattan
hotel.  The two sides will meet again next week, Kessler said. The NBA 
locked out its players on July 1.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jay Beberman at 
 jbeberman@bloomberg.net  